ous Corporation: Part I [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkU2O4yAQRk8Td=
o74x16wmM1cwypD2UFtgwXlGaVP3yRZtIRARVF6nx4BCLdSn_4sjdhrm-l5os_4v-1IhJVdDeuc=
ohdWjsroiUWvoxjNyFKb14p4QNo91QvZeS17CkCp5PcE59Kwhw92nFAYKY2SCuwalZm4UM4KrWJ=
Q_MOFKybMAT3-w_osGdnuH0Rnu6k_N_m3ryVRKCkfsMF3yngP5ei3hOGRO3V_vSiFGlU4z5S3AY=
aIAXOv9_SNcYCLSi5HudoQSj1LfScdTqg0pKEHmqzW0mmWvORScCWlkMYIfhd34ZZouBZWA-dO2=
YUHu67TKoNeOUx40_zY5L1dSyMIX69srPpcaCm1Z-ntrwccuL8b3dPcz-PKiZ4zZlh2jB-F9PmJ=
t9R5w4w9JMYZqPvvcOGcMM7Zj7LuWGkhlXUj6-RY-lT-hf4A2zOg5w], in which he asks a=
nd attempts to answer the question:=C2=A0
Can we approach the problem from the other direction: even if we still need=
 human beings to perform certain specialized tasks, can we remove the manag=
ement from the equation instead?
In the post, Vitalik refers to Bitshares=E2=80=99 founder Daniel Larimer's =
idea [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkcuO4yAQRb8m7GwBxsZZsJjN_EHWFo8i=
oWODBeXu9t9PdTJSSwikKl2dq4O3CPdST7OXhuznWvDcwWT4aisgQmVHg7qkYMQk52FUVxaMCmI=
eZ5baEivAZtNqsB7A9sOtyVtMJb8SnMuRPYycopDjzJ1X3k1CK829DB6k4o4HiG-uPUKC7MHAJ9=
SzZGCreSDu7TL8uci_dKhQQ7s-XUJfUu592WiaWvd_0BVK7vZM-d7FUrto1wZdA3_UhOdFDv3tA=
9MNr98n_2LJSC4FH6SkcqPgveiFdmHkSkzKcq6HyXE_xXiN0qvI7RUuim932bfDUQ___CnAqskF=
XakEpfXzYTdYXwuSsdC7HZngC2TrVghvT_jW_TK33CFDpW8Ii0WSTHChtRi1nt5eSOSghBwmPTM=
ih0Kp_Av9BzSRmKs] that Bitcoin is actually a sort of a proto-DAO, a new kin=
d of decentralized equivalent to a traditional company:=C2=A0
Shares =E2=89=88 Bitcoin=C2=A0
Shareholders =E2=89=88 Bitcoin owners=C2=A0
Employees =E2=89=88 Miners and validators=C2=A0
Payroll =E2=89=88=C2=A0 Bitcoin rewards for adding blocks to the chain=C2=
=A0
Marketing=C2=A0 =E2=89=88 All of those people with laser eyes pumping Bitco=
in
But Bitcoin is limited. It=E2=80=99s kind of dumb. It doesn=E2=80=99t reall=
y know much, can=E2=80=99t really change itself, and doesn=E2=80=99t really=
 do anything; =E2=80=9Cit simply exists, and leaves it up to the world to r=
ecognize it.=E2=80=9D It really is like gold in that it sits there as peopl=
e do stuff to it and assign value to it.=C2=A0
More charitably, to analogize with an equally complex analogy (this is the =
nice thing about having smart readers!), if Bitcoin is like Artificial Narr=
ow Intelligence (ANI), DAOs are like Artificial General Intelligence (AGI).=
 Bitcoin does the thing that it was programmed to do really well, but DAOs =
can theoretically do anything really well.=C2=A0
Vitalik said as much when he introduced Ethereum:=C2=A0
What Ethereum intends to provide is a blockchain with a built-in fully fled=
ged Turing-complete programming language that can be used to create "contra=
cts" that can be used to encode arbitrary state transition functions, allow=
ing users to create any of the systems described above, as well as many oth=
ers that we have not yet imagined, simply by writing up the logic in a few =
lines of code.
Bitcoin is digital money. Ethereum is a platform on top of which builders c=
an create anything, from apps to entire organizations.=C2=A0
Ethereum, Bitcoin, and other blockchains are Layer 1 in the Web3 tech stack=
=2E For Bitcoin, all of the magic happen=
s at Layer 1, but with Ethereum, most=
 of the magic happens in Layer 2, the protocol and smart contracts layer.=
=C2=A0
Source: readthedocs.io, examples mine
The second layer is where builders create Lego blocks of protocols and smar=
t contracts that can be arranged in countless combinations and formations t=
o do anything from mint art to trade crypto, directly, without the need for=
 a third-party.=C2=A0
